  "dateModified": "2026-04-02",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Abscisic acid: a C₁₅ terpenoid hormone primarily regulating water-stress responses. Despite its name — historically derived from its role in abscission (leaf/fruit drop) — ABA is not the primary driver of abscission (that role belongs to ethylene). Instead, ABA is the plant\u0026rsquo;s central drought and stress-response hormone, coordinating stomatal closure, seed dormancy, and tolerance mechanisms across tissues. ABA accumulates rapidly in response to water deficit, activating a cascade that prioritizes survival over growth.\n",
  "keywords": "botany, plant-physiology, plant-hormones, stress-response, drought",
  "name": "Abscisic Acid",
